programming_language.default-parameters:
*General-Programming-Knowledge*


            There are no default parameters in C. 


            But one way to achieve this is by passing NULL pointers and 
            then set the values to the default if NULL is passed.



0   

1   //Example of function with default parameters in C:

2   

3   void OpenFile(char *path)

4   {

5       FILE *outHandle;

6   

7       if (path==NULL)

8       {

9           outHandle=fopen("DummyFile", "w");

10      }

11      else

12      {

13          outHandle=fopen(path, "w");

14      }

15  }

16  

17  int main()

18  {

19      char* filePath;

20      OpenFile(filePath);

21  }

