programming_language.concurrent-programming:
*General-Programming-Knowledge*


            Multithreading in Java:



            In Java: Threads can be created by using two mechanisms : 




            1. Extending the Thread class; 

            2. Implementing the Runnable Interface;




            Thread creation by extending the Thread class:



            We create a class that extends the java.lang.Thread class. 
            This class overrides the run() method available in 
            the Thread class.



            A thread begins its life inside run() method. 
            We create an object of our 
            new class and call start() method to start the 
            execution of a thread. 
            Start() invokes the run() method on the Thread object.



0   

1   //Example of multithreading in Java 

2   //by extending the Thread class:

3   

4   class MultithreadingDemo extends Thread 

5   {

6       public void run()

7       {

8           try 

9           {

10              // Displaying the thread that is running

11              System.out.println(

12                  "Thread " + Thread.currentThread().getId()

13                  + " is running");

14          }

15          catch (Exception e) 

16          {

17              // Throwing an exception

18              System.out.println("Exception is caught");

19          }

20      }

21  }

22   

23  // Main Class

24  public class Multithread {

25      public static void main(String[] args)

26      {

27          int n = 8; // Number of threads

28          for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) 

29          {

30              MultithreadingDemo object

31                  = new MultithreadingDemo();

32              object.start();

33          }

34      }

35  }

36  


        Thread creation by implementing the Runnable Interface



        We create a new class which implements java.lang.Runnable 
        interface and override run() 
        method. 


        Then we instantiate a Thread object and call 
        start() method on this object. 



0   

1   //Example of multithreading in Java 

2   //by implementing the Runnable interface:

3   

4   class MultithreadingDemo implements Runnable 

5   {

6       public void run()

7       {

8           try 

9           {

10              // Displaying the thread that is running

11              System.out.println(

12                  "Thread " + Thread.currentThread().getId()

13                  + " is running");

14          }

15          catch (Exception e) 

16          {

17              // Throwing an exception

18              System.out.println("Exception is caught");

19          }

20      }

21  }

22   

23  // Main Class

24  class Multithread 

25  {

26      public static void main(String[] args)

27      {

28          int n = 8; // Number of threads

29          for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) 

30          {

31              Thread object

32                  = new Thread(new MultithreadingDemo());

33              object.start();

34          }

35      }

36  }

